.TH "sdw_enable_disable_slave_ports" 9 "sdw_enable_disable_slave_ports" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sdw_enable_disable_slave_ports \- Enable/disable slave data port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sdw_enable_disable_slave_ports
.BI "(struct sdw_bus *bus "  ","
.BI "struct sdw_slave_runtime *s_rt "  ","
.BI "struct sdw_port_runtime *p_rt "  ","
.BI "bool en "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bus" 12
bus instance
.IP "s_rt" 12
slave runtime
.IP "p_rt" 12
port runtime
.IP "en" 12
enable or disable operation
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function only sets the enable/disable bits in the relevant bank, the
actual enable/disable is done with a bank switch
